It was whose decree?

26:58.152 --> 27:01.454
I'm surprised you have to ask.

27:01.456 --> 27:03.689
After all, you were the one who convinced

27:03.691 --> 27:05.558
your siblings to consecrate her

27:05.560 --> 27:09.028
in New Orleans soil.

27:09.030 --> 27:10.563
Esther.

27:13.400 --> 27:15.201
So not even death can stop my mother

27:15.203 --> 27:17.036
from seeking the annihilation

27:17.038 --> 27:20.206
of her own flesh and blood.

27:20.208 --> 27:22.341
This isn't the end.

27:22.343 --> 27:24.577
As long as that child lives,

27:24.579 --> 27:25.911
the witches of New Orleans

27:25.913 --> 27:27.746
will never stop coming for it.

27:27.748 --> 27:31.450
Esther will never stop coming for it.

27:31.452 --> 27:33.352
It has been decreed.

27:33.354 --> 27:35.020
Your baby will be consecrated

27:35.022 --> 27:36.255
among her ancestors.

27:36.257 --> 27:38.257
She will not live.

27:40.293 --> 27:42.728
They're coming for me.

27:42.730 --> 27:44.229
I can feel it.

27:44.231 --> 27:46.932
I've failed them.

27:46.934 --> 27:52.471
Please. Understand, I just wanted to live.

27:52.473 --> 27:56.408
Tell Klaus...

27:56.410 --> 27:58.243
I'm sorry.

27:58.245 --> 28:01.079
[Coughing]

28:07.754 --> 28:09.321
I'm not.

28:24.170 --> 28:27.105
Klaus: We should have felt
our mother's hand in this.

28:27.107 --> 28:28.940
We should have known she would not be bound

28:28.942 --> 28:30.942
by anything as obvious as death,

28:30.944 --> 28:33.945
and now she has control of the witches.

28:33.947 --> 28:36.548
- They will never stop.
- No.

28:36.550 --> 28:38.516
Nor would I expect the
Guerrera Wolves to back down.

28:38.518 --> 28:41.786
Hayley and the child are wolf royalty,

28:41.788 --> 28:44.055
and as such, they are a threat

28:44.057 --> 28:47.092
to Francesca's claim to leadership.

28:47.094 --> 28:48.793
They will never be safe.

28:51.297 --> 28:53.965
What was it you said to me earlier,

28:53.967 --> 28:57.268
that I've made enemies
every day of my miserable life?

28:57.270 --> 29:02.240
Well, the worst of them are
within these borders, brother.

29:02.242 --> 29:03.741
I have brought into the world

29:03.743 --> 29:05.577
a weapon they can use against me.

29:05.579 --> 29:07.513
Then we will arm ourselves.

29:07.526 --> 29:11.482
Brother, we've fought every adversary
in this town and we have won,

29:11.484 --> 29:12.984
and we'll fight them again,

29:12.986 --> 29:14.719
no matter who they are.

29:14.721 --> 29:16.955
We'll make this home a fortress.

29:16.957 --> 29:19.957
I will not have her live
her life as a prisoner.

29:19.959 --> 29:22.627
Then we leave here together, all of us.

29:22.629 --> 29:24.862
Wherever we go,

29:24.864 --> 29:26.497
however far we run,

29:26.499 --> 29:29.367
those who seek power
and revenge will hunt us,

29:29.369 --> 29:32.770
they will hunt her.

29:32.772 --> 29:34.539
She has inherited all our enemies

29:34.541 --> 29:36.174
with none of our defenses.

29:36.176 --> 29:37.842
So whether we stay or we leave,

29:37.844 --> 29:39.177
we condemn her.

29:39.179 --> 29:41.045
Hayley: There is a third option.

29:44.449 --> 29:47.685
I grew up in a war zone.

29:47.687 --> 29:50.454
My parents thought they could protect me,

29:50.456 --> 29:52.623
but in the end, they were slaughtered,

29:52.625 --> 29:57.261
and I spent my childhood alone and unloved.

30:03.869 --> 30:07.271
I made a promise to
my baby and to myself...

30:09.474 --> 30:12.877
That she would not grow up like I did,

30:12.879 --> 30:16.814
that she would grow up safe and loved,

30:16.816 --> 30:19.483
and yet here she is on
her first day in this world

30:19.485 --> 30:24.254
with a grandmother that
is bent on sacrificing her

30:24.256 --> 30:27.157
and a mother that has to drink the blood

30:27.159 --> 30:29.727
of her own baby to survive transitioning

30:29.729 --> 30:32.196
into a hybrid,

30:32.198 --> 30:35.099
and I'm the one that loves her the most.

30:42.707 --> 30:47.010
I think the only thing to do is

30:47.012 --> 30:49.813
send her away while we stay behind

30:49.815 --> 30:53.116
and clean up the mess that we've made.

30:54.698 --> 30:57.621
No. This is insane.

30:57.623 --> 30:59.122
You heard Genevieve.

30:59.124 --> 31:02.926
So long as she lives,
that baby will be hunted.

31:07.131 --> 31:11.201
Not if no one knows she lives.

31:11.203 --> 31:13.503
What is it that you intend to do, brother?

31:13.505 --> 31:15.939
Whatever it takes

31:15.941 --> 31:19.342
to save our family.

31:21.213 --> 31:23.713
Today begins a new day in the quarter.

31:23.715 --> 31:25.649
My family, long-time residents

31:25.651 --> 31:28.919
of this great community,

31:28.921 --> 31:30.887
pledges to help every citizen recover

31:30.889 --> 31:34.424
from the terrible outbreak of gang violence

31:34.426 --> 31:38.361
that erupted on the streets
of our city last night.

31:38.363 --> 31:40.764
We will rebuild.

31:40.766 --> 31:43.900
We will remember those who perished

31:43.902 --> 31:46.102
as we seek to disinfect this town

31:46.104 --> 31:47.771
of its worst elements.

31:47.773 --> 31:49.405
We will work together

31:49.407 --> 31:53.710
to ensure the heart of the Crescent City

31:53.712 --> 31:55.211
thrives again.

32:07.324 --> 32:09.325
Last man standing, huh?

32:11.528 --> 32:13.463
I'm interested in making a deal.

32:13.465 --> 32:15.031
Don't look like you got much to offer.

32:15.033 --> 32:16.866
I'm hearing word that the Guerreras want

32:16.868 --> 32:18.701
the quarter to be a no vampire zone.

32:18.703 --> 32:20.136
I can make that happen

32:20.138 --> 32:21.804
in exchange for you leaving us alone

32:21.806 --> 32:25.641
across the river, or...

32:25.643 --> 32:28.878
I can unleash hell on your new wolf pack.

32:30.814 --> 32:32.014
And how can you do that?

32:32.016 --> 32:35.418
Easy. I made my peace with Klaus.

32:35.420 --> 32:36.719
He cured me.

32:36.721 --> 32:40.189
So now it's you versus us.

32:40.191 --> 32:42.358
Klaus...

32:42.360 --> 32:45.294
Is a warmonger.

32:45.296 --> 32:47.363
You think he's gonna choose to side

32:47.365 --> 32:52.034
with a pack of scrawny vamps

32:52.036 --> 32:53.502
or an army of the new wolf breed

32:53.504 --> 32:55.237
that he created?

32:55.239 --> 32:57.807
I'm thinking he's gonna side with us,

32:57.809 --> 32:59.375
especially after he finds out

32:59.377 --> 33:02.945
that your pack killed his kid.

33:04.114 --> 33:05.681
What?

33:07.384 --> 33:08.484
Open the box

33:08.486 --> 33:09.885
and let me know what you think

33:09.887 --> 33:11.220
Klaus will believe about who's responsible

33:11.222 --> 33:13.422
for what you find inside of it.

33:20.230 --> 33:22.698
Cremation may be the best way to go

33:22.700 --> 33:25.400
before Klaus smells it on you.

33:42.652 --> 33:42.918
Cremation may be the best way to go

33:45.028 --> 33:48.005
[Music playing]

34:07.370 --> 34:08.871
Cami: Klaus.

34:14.210 --> 34:16.245
Your baby?

34:16.246 --> 34:18.380
She died

34:18.382 --> 34:22.650
a few hours after the Guerrera attack.

34:22.652 --> 34:24.585
This is...

34:24.588 --> 34:25.721
This is all my fault.

34:25.723 --> 34:27.922
I can assure you it is not.

34:27.925 --> 34:30.092
No. If I hadn't hesitated,

34:30.094 --> 34:31.627
I could have uncovered Francesca's plot

34:31.629 --> 34:33.094
in time to stop it.

34:33.097 --> 34:34.563
And how would you have
stopped the coven of witches

34:34.565 --> 34:37.498
in league with her?

34:37.501 --> 34:40.302
No.

34:40.304 --> 34:45.507
If anyone is to blame, I am.

34:47.743 --> 34:51.612
I am so... So sorry.

34:55.418 --> 34:57.118
Camille...

35:00.222 --> 35:02.924
I appreciate you being here,

35:02.926 --> 35:05.126
but we cannot be friends.

35:05.128 --> 35:06.761
What?

35:07.997 --> 35:10.632
You had me pegged from the start,

35:10.634 --> 35:12.834
a man damaged by his demons,

35:12.836 --> 35:14.002
and those demons are not dormant.

35:14.004 --> 35:16.738
They are hell-bent on killing me

35:16.740 --> 35:19.474
and everything I find beautiful...

35:21.210 --> 35:22.877
And you...

35:25.147 --> 35:27.615
You are beautiful.

35:30.686 --> 35:33.621
Please, please just go.

35:33.623 --> 35:34.989
Klaus.

35:36.492 --> 35:37.959
Go.

35:58.347 --> 36:00.448
Did Marcel play his part?

36:00.450 --> 36:02.717
He managed to locate a stillborn baby

36:02.719 --> 36:04.886
in a hospital in upstate Louisiana.

36:04.888 --> 36:06.721
I trust he agreed to the terms.

36:06.723 --> 36:08.956
He has agreed to allow me to compel him

36:08.958 --> 36:12.226
to forget what he knows of my child.

36:12.228 --> 36:14.996
In exchange, he wants vials of my blood.

36:14.998 --> 36:17.631
The witches will have to believe this.

36:17.633 --> 36:21.001
Soon that fourth
harvest girl will resurrect.

36:21.003 --> 36:23.237
The coven will rebuild.

36:23.239 --> 36:24.738
If they sense that your child lives,

36:24.740 --> 36:26.006
they will hunt her.

36:26.008 --> 36:30.177
The witches will buy what we sell.

36:30.179 --> 36:32.746
We just have to sell it properly.

36:42.023 --> 36:45.092
Then all that remains is to say goodbye.

36:45.094 --> 36:47.928
[Music playing]

36:49.898 --> 36:52.733
[Baby cooing]

36:54.069 --> 36:56.370
[Cries]

37:06.481 --> 37:08.982
[Crying]

37:30.204 --> 37:33.073
Klaus, voice-over:
They will be watching us,

37:33.075 --> 37:36.042
all of them.

37:36.044 --> 37:40.447
The 3 of us leaving together
will draw too much attention.

37:40.449 --> 37:42.182
I will go alone.

37:43.918 --> 37:47.387
Take your mourning public when I'm gone.

37:47.389 --> 37:49.923
Elijah, voice-over: I don't imagine
that will be too difficult.

37:52.126 --> 37:55.695
Grief, after all, is grief.

38:00.768 --> 38:04.738
In what world will she be safe without us?

38:04.740 --> 38:07.207
Who can protect her better than we?

38:09.009 --> 38:10.710
There is one person.

38:23.691 --> 38:25.558
Hello, sister.

38:32.766 --> 38:35.034
She looks like her mother.

38:37.371 --> 38:39.205
Maybe there is a God after all.

38:41.975 --> 38:45.344
Well, she has a hint
of the devil in her eyes.

38:46.914 --> 38:48.581
That's all me.

38:52.819 --> 38:55.021
You'll need a witch you can trust

38:55.023 --> 38:56.589
to cast a cloaking spell.

38:56.591 --> 38:57.790
I'll get one.

38:57.792 --> 38:59.358
No one can ever find her.

38:59.360 --> 39:00.826
I know what to do, Nik.

39:00.828 --> 39:03.929
[Cooing]

39:03.931 --> 39:06.499
Perhaps we'll get a white fence.

39:06.501 --> 39:08.834
I think that would be lovely.

39:20.480 --> 39:23.549
This city would have seen you dead,

39:23.551 --> 39:26.819
but I will have it your home,

39:26.821 --> 39:31.523
and every soul who wishes you harm

39:31.525 --> 39:33.559
will be struck down.

39:33.561 --> 39:38.030
Just as sure as my blood
runs in your veins,

39:38.032 --> 39:42.034
you will return to me.

39:46.740 --> 39:49.241
[Cooing]

40:04.591 --> 40:06.591
In spite of our differences, Rebekah,

40:06.593 --> 40:10.595
there is no one I would trust
more with my daughter's life.

40:16.969 --> 40:20.305
Be happy... Sister.

40:21.541 --> 40:24.442
She will be happy, Nik, I promise.

40:25.978 --> 40:27.612
What's her name?

40:32.118 --> 40:33.785
Hope.

40:36.022 --> 40:38.323
Her name is Hope.

41:25.137 --> 41:28.039
May you rest in peace.

41:28.041 --> 41:30.141
What's the fun in that?

41:32.211 --> 41:34.212
Come along.

41:34.214 --> 41:36.013
We have much to do.

41:37.460 --> 41:38.983
Yes mother.

